  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of anxiety?",
  "response": "Anxiety can manifest in many different ways and can vary from person to person, but some common symptoms include:\n\n1. Excessive worry or fear: People with anxiety may worry excessively about everyday situations, or have intense fear about specific things or events.\n\n2. Restlessness or feeling on edge: People with anxiety may have a hard time relaxing and feel restless or on edge, as if something bad is going to happen.\n\n3. Difficulty concentrating: Anxiety can make it hard to focus or concentrate on tasks, leading to a decrease in productivity.\n\n4. Irritability: People with anxiety may be easily irritated or have a short temper, which can strain relationships with others.\n\n5. Muscle tension: Anxiety can cause muscles to tense up, leading to headaches, body aches, and other physical symptoms.\n\n6. Sleep problems: Anxiety can cause difficulty falling or staying asleep, or lead to restless and unsatisfying sleep.\n\n7. Fatigue: The constant worry and fear associated with anxiety can be exhausting, leading to feelings of fatigue and low energy.\n\n8. Panic attacks: In some cases, anxiety can lead to sudden and intense episodes of fear known as panic attacks, which can cause symptoms such as heart palpitations, sweating, trembling, and shortness of breath.\n\nIf you are experiencing any of these symptoms, it may be helpful to talk to a mental health professional for support and guidance.",
